glosses: to shovel up, clear something away with a shovel

etymology:
From Ottoman Turkish كورهمك (küremek, “to shovel up or away”), from Old Anatolian Turkish [script needed] (kürü-, “to dig up”), from Proto-Turkic *küre-.
Cognates
Cognate with Karakhanid [script needed] (kürīmēk, “to dig up, shovel”), Azerbaijani kürümək (“to shovel”), Bashkir көрәү (körəw, “to rake”), Khakas кӱрирге (kürirge, “to rake, shovel”), Kazakh күреу (küreu, “to rake, shovel”), Kyrgyz күрөө (küröö, “to shovel”), Yakut күрт (kürt, “to shovel”).
